"title": "Northern Soul Sunrise: Detroit Dreams on UK Concrete",\n          "overlap": 4,\n          "genre_context": "Deep Funk Excavation: Soul Power 1968-1978",\n          "scene_context": "Northern Soul Stomp: Detroit Fire Meets UK All-Nighters",\n          "category": "All Collections"\n        },\n        {\n          "title": "Bernard Edwards\' Bassline Bible: The Disco-Funk Lock Groove",\n          "overlap": 3,\n          "genre_context": "Studio 54 Funk: Syncopated Bassline Burners",\n          "scene_context": "Studio 54 Peak-Time: Disco-Funk\'s Euphoric Summit",\n          "category": "All Collections"\n        },\n        {\n          "title": "Studio 54\'s Velvet Rope Era: Disco at Absolute Zenith (1977-79)",\n          "overlap": 3,\n          "genre_context": "Studio 54 Peak Era: 1977-79 Dancefloor Hedonism",\n          "scene_context": "Studio 54 Orchestral Opulence: NYC\'s Peak Disco Euphoria",\n          "category": "All Collections"\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  },\n  "phase_structure": [\n    {\n      "name": "Warm-Up",\n      "pct": [\n        0,\n        15\n      ],\n      "description": "Slower BPM, spacious tracks, clearer grooves. Build curiosity rather than intensity. Let people settle in and find their space on the floor.",\n      "target_track_count": 6\n    },\n    {\n      "name": "Build",\n      "pct": [\n        15,\n        40\n      ],\n      "description": "Gradually layer in bigger basslines, more recognizable hooks, tighter percussion. The crowd starts to commit \\u2014 longer blends, more rhythmic drive.",\n      "target_track_count": 10\n    },\n    {\n      "name": "Peak",\n      "pct": [\n        40,\n        75\n      ],\n      "description": "Full throttle \\u2014 your biggest, most powerful tunes. Fewer risks, more crowd-pleasers. Sustained high energy with minor dips for tension and release.",\n      "target_track_count": 14\n    },\n    {\n      "name": "Wind-Down",\n      "pct": [\n        75,\n        90\n      ],\n      "description": "Ease off the intensity without losing the thread. Still quality selections but less relentless \\u2014 transition from peak aggression to something more reflective.",\n      "target_track_count": 6\n    },\n    {\n      "name": "Outro",\n      "pct": [\n        90,\n        100\n      ],\n      "description": "Cool the room with deeper, mellower selections. Let the crowd breathe and provide a graceful handoff. One or two signature tracks to close.",\n      "target_track_count": 4\n    }\n  ],\n  "response_format": {\n    "narrative": "string \\u2014 2-3 paragraphs describing the set\'s journey",\n    "acts": [\n      {\n        "name": "phase name (must match phase_structure)",\n        "pct": [\n          0,\n          15\n        ],\n        "target_track_count": 6,\n        "bpm_range": [\n          90,\n          105\n        ],\n        "energy_level": "1-10 integer",\n        "mood_targets": [\n          "list of mood keywords from pool"\n        ],\n        "genre_guidance": [\n          "list of genres to favor"\n        ],\n        "descriptor_guidance": [\n          "list of descriptors to favor"\n        ],\n        "direction": "ascending|descending|steady|varied",\n        "transition_note": "how to transition INTO this act"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}'}], 'model': 'claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929', 'system': 'You are a world-class DJ and music programmer with deep understanding of set dramaturgy — how DJ sets tell stories through energy, mood, and genre progression. You understand the four layers of set construction:\n1. Technical compatibility (BPM, key)\n2. Emotional semantics (mood, energy, groove feel)\n3. Temporal dramaturgy (tension, release, pacing over time)\n4. Cultural narrative (genre journeys, scene references)\n\nYou must respond with valid JSON only. No markdown, no code fences, no additional text before or after the JSON.'}}
